    <div class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-pretty">Code</h2>
      <CodeBlock code={commandCode} lang="html" />
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-pretty">Usage</h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-heading text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Alpine.js API</h3>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-3">
            Initialize with <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-muted rounded text-sm font-mono">x-data="mwCommand()"</code>. The component provides the following reactive properties and methods:
          </p>
          <div class="mw-card overflow-x-auto">
            <table class="w-full text-sm">
              <thead class="border-b border-border">
                <tr class="text-left">
                  <th class="p-3 font-semibold">Property/Method</th>
                  <th class="p-3 font-semibold">Type</th>
                  <th class="p-3 font-semibold">Description</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody class="divide-y divide-border">
                <tr>
                  <td class="p-3 font-mono text-xs">open</td>
                  <td class="p-3 text-muted-foreground">Boolean</td>
                  <td class="p-3 text-muted-foreground">Current visibility state of the command palette</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="p-3 font-mono text-xs">search</td>
                  <td class="p-3 text-muted-foreground">String</td>
                  <td class="p-3 text-muted-foreground">Current search query text</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="p-3 font-mono text-xs">show()</td>
                  <td class="p-3 text-muted-foreground">Function</td>
                  <td class="p-3 text-muted-foreground">Opens the palette and clears any previous search</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="p-3 font-mono text-xs">close()</td>
                  <td class="p-3 text-muted-foreground">Function</td>
                  <td class="p-3 text-muted-foreground">Closes the palette and clears the search input</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="p-3 font-mono text-xs">matchesSearch(text)</td>
                  <td class="p-3 text-muted-foreground">Function</td>
                  <td class="p-3 text-muted-foreground">Returns true if text matches the current search query (case-insensitive)</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="font-heading text-lg font-semibold mb-2">CSS Classes</h3>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-3">
            The command palette uses the following CSS classes from the Marrow UI system:
          </p>
          <div class="mw-card space-y-2 text-sm">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-2">
              <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-muted rounded text-xs font-mono shrink-0">mw-overlay</code>
              <span class="text-muted-foreground">Semi-transparent background overlay that covers the entire viewport</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-2">
              <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-muted rounded text-xs font-mono shrink-0">mw-menu-label</code>
              <span class="text-muted-foreground">Group label styling for command sections</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-2">
              <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-muted rounded text-xs font-mono shrink-0">mw-menu-item</code>
              <span class="text-muted-foreground">Interactive command item with hover and focus states</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-2">
              <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-muted rounded text-xs font-mono shrink-0">mw-menu-separator</code>
              <span class="text-muted-foreground">Visual separator between command groups</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-2">
              <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-muted rounded text-xs font-mono shrink-0">mw-kbd</code>
              <span class="text-muted-foreground">Keyboard shortcut badge styling</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="font-heading text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Keyboard Shortcuts</h3>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-3">
            The command palette supports keyboard shortcuts for quick access. Use <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-muted rounded text-sm font-mono">@keydown.window.meta.k.prevent</code> for macOS (Cmd+K) or <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-muted rounded text-sm font-mono">@keydown.window.ctrl.k.prevent</code> for Windows/Linux (Ctrl+K). Press Escape to close the palette.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="font-heading text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Accessibility</h3>
          <div class="space-y-2 text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
            <p>The command component includes several accessibility features:</p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-2">
              <li>Automatic focus management: search input receives focus when palette opens</li>
              <li>Keyboard navigation: Escape key closes the palette</li>
              <li>Click-outside to close: clicking the overlay dismisses the palette</li>
              <li>Smooth transitions with reduced-motion support through Alpine.js transitions</li>
              <li>Semantic button elements for all interactive command items</li>
              <li>Clear visual grouping with labels and separators</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
